The chain with kernel $Q$ is:

 **ergodic** if $\lim_{n\to\infty}\|Q^n(y,\cdot)-\mu\|_{TV}=0$ for all $y\in\mathcal Y$;

 **geometrically ergodic** if there exists $r>1$ such that $\sum_{n=1}^\infty r^n\|Q^n(y,\cdot)-\mu\|_{TV}<\infty$ for all $y$;

 **uniformly ergodic** if $\lim_{n\to\infty}\sup_{y\in\mathcal Y}\|Q^n(y,\cdot)-\mu\|_{TV}=0$.
